18/03/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu and visiting Croatian counterpart Stipe Mesic reaffirmed on Friday (March 16th) the goal of Euro-Atlantic integration shared by their countries, as well as their common commitment to dialogue and regional stability. Mesic also met with Albanian Prime Minister Sali Berisha, who agreed that Albania and Croatia should strengthen collaboration, particularly as regards aspirations for NATO membership, under the framework of the US-Adriatic Charter initiative, as well as boosting economic ties. Mesic also voiced Croatia's readiness to assist Albania in implementing its Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. (Albanian News, HRT - 17/03/07; Albanian President website - 16/03/07)
